replies.body:
would never invest gold into this.

the idea of taking less damage from higher leveled opponents is pretty good. having it destroyed and losing those 600 gold makes it a noob trap. enemies who are ahead of you are very likely to be able to destroy the thing every time you buy it.

the better approach would be to make it a low cost, cost efficient/slot inefficient item that you would grab for momentary power when behind, and feel compelled to sell later on for a bigger item. very similar to {{item:1055}}
